"'''Conflict of Interest'''" is a short story written by [[Laurie Burns]] that was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 13|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 13]] by [[West End Games]] in May 1997.

It was later published in ''[[Tales from the New Republic]]''.

Set in [[7 ABY/Legends|7 ABY]], 3 years after [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']], this was a 31-page story about a [[Gender/Legends|female]] undercover named [[Selby Jarrad]].

==Plot summary==
[[New Republic Intelligence Service|New Republic Intelligence]] [[Agent/Legends|agent]] [[Selby Jarrad]] goes undercover as a business woman on the [[Bacta/Legends|bacta]]-producing [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Verkuyl]]. She intends to meet and sway [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Governor/Legends|governor]] [[Parco Ein]] into surrendering control of the planet to its populace, which stands at the brink of revolt. Her aims run counter to [[Daven Quarle]]'s, the governor's aide, and her supposedly sympathetic contact within the government. A native of the planet, Quarle believes the Imperial presence stabilized Verkuyl, and that its populace is not ready for self-determination. His attempts to scuttle the operation fail, and the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] ultimately arrives and backs the revolt, though Jarrad has doubts if the planet truly is in better hands. 

